      <title>Acts As Threaded</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.railtie.net/"&gt;Bob Silva&lt;/a&gt; who has been a &lt;a href="http://dev.rubyonrails.org/ticket/3158"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://dev.rubyonrails.org/ticket/3743"&gt;on&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href="http://dev.rubyonrails.org"&gt;Rails Trac System&lt;/a&gt; and core list as of late has just released a screencast of his newest toy, &lt;a href="http://www.railtie.net/articles/2006/02/05/rails-acts_as_threaded-plugin"&gt;acts_as_threaded&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Acts as threaded allows you to created threaded entries (like a forum) easily and without the hassle of dealing with acts_as_nested_set and such.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Go check it out. Thanks alot Bob! Good work.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
